Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box on Page 03
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Penis, infection/inflammation' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'Regional extension' radio button is enabled
And 'At least scrotal expansion' radio button is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Distension' checkbox is enabled
And 'Air inclusions' checkbox is enabled
And 'Circumscribed fluid accumulation' checkbox is enabled

And 'Focal plaques of the tunica albuginea' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fascial thickening' checkbox is enabled

And 'Fluid around prosthesis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Prosthesis defect' checkbox is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' checkbox is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' checkbox is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Circumscribed fluid accumulation' checkbox
Then 'Abcess' checkbox is enabled
And 'Scrotal expansion' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Abcess' checkbox
Then 'Expansion in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Focal plaques of the tunica albuginea' checkbox
Then 'T1w hypointense' checkbox is enabled
And 'T2w hypointense' checkbox is enabled
And 'Exemplary thickness in mm' input field is enabled
And 'Corpus cavernosum right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus cavernosum left' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus spongiosum' checkbox is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal signal voids' checkbox is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
